# Icons (MingCute + Iconify)

- Use **`@iconify/react`** with **`@iconify-icons/mingcute`** (named imports per icon).
- Prefer **named imports** from `@iconify-icons/mingcute/<name>-line` or `<name>-fill`; avoid standalone string IDs like `"mingcute:..."` (bundle/tree-shaking).
- **Naming**: The path suffix is **`-fill`** (not `filled`). “Filled” describes the look; imports always use the **`-fill`** module (pair with the same base name as `-line`, e.g. `add-line` ↔ `add-fill`).
- **Hover**: For any **interactive** control that shows an icon (button, link, tab, list row, etc.), default the icon to **`-line`**, and on **`:hover` (and `:focus-visible` when it is focusable)** swap to the matching **`-fill`** icon so the affordance strengthens. Hide/show or swap `icon={...}` in React; keep both imports. Non-interactive decorative icons can stay single-variant.
- **Consistency**: Within one block (header, card, modal), keep **line vs fill** coherent; **nav / toolbar / filters** default to **line** at rest, **fill** on hover/focus as above.
- **Color**: Prefer inheriting from parent text (`currentColor`) via CSS over hardcoding `color` on `<Icon>` when possible.
- **Alignment**: With labels, use `inline-flex`, `align-items: center`, and a small `gap`.
- **Size**: Tabs / toolbar / filters typically **16–20px**; match surrounding type and tap targets.
- **A11y**: Meaningful controls get `aria-label`; decorative icons can use `aria-hidden` when appropriate.
- **States**: Style default / hover / active / disabled so icon affordances stay clear (opacity, contrast, pointer). Prefer **line → fill** on hover/focus for icons per **Hover** above; use opacity or `pointer-events` for disabled.
- After adding or changing icons in UI work, **summarize at the end of the reply** which icon was used for what.
